eNCA Zimbabwe correspondent Pindai Dube reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 HARARE - Two MPs belonging to Zimbabwe’s main opposition, Citizens Coalition for Change party, are spending the weekend in jail. They're accused of organising a funeral session at the home of slain fellow party member, Moreblessing Ali. Job Sikhala and Godfrey Sithole are charged with public violence. Police allege that the funeral session led to public violence in the area. * eNCA's Zimbabwe correspondent Pindai Dube reports.